body:
The `iopodman.Create` as follow:

```go
type Create struct {
    // ...
    Entrypoint             *string   `json:"entrypoint,omitempty"`
    Env                    *[]string `json:"env,omitempty"`
    // ...
}
```
IMHO, the struct is hard to use.

comments.body:
> It makes a distinction between the empty string, "", and completely unset. A nil means the setting should be left as default, a "" overrides it with the empty string. The two have very different meanings in some places.

It seems less needed. For example:

```go
func stringArrayFromVarlink(v []string, flagName string, defaultValue []string) CRStringArray {
	cr := CRStringArray{}
	if v == nil {
		cr.Val = []string{}
		if defaultValue != nil {
			cr.Val = defaultValue
		}
		cr.Changed = false
	} else {
		cr.Val = v
		cr.Changed = true
	}
	cr.Flag = flagName
	return cr
}

func stringFromVarlink(v string, flagName string, defaultValue string) CRString {
	cr := CRString{}
	if v == "" {
		if defaultValue != "" {
			cr.Val = defaultValue
		}
		cr.Changed = false
	} else {
		cr.Val = v
		cr.Changed = true
	}
	cr.Flag = flagName
	return cr
}
```

If really needed, the following struct is looked good to me:

```go
 type NullString struct { 
 	String  string 
 	Valid bool 
 } 
```
🤔
